    <node id="RAG-Anything Environment Specification List (list)">
      <data key="d0">RAG-Anything Environment Specification List (list)</data>
      <data key="d1">list</data>
      <data key="d2">A text-based list enumerating technical environment specifications for the RAG-Anything validation setup. It identifies the conda environment name, installation method, default text parser, and available office tooling. This list item serves as a critical validation node within a non-Office document designed to verify local parsing capabilities without API dependencies. It establishes the local software stack requirements and toolchain configuration essential for reproducing the system environment on target hardware.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-411cf019ba107d055b1ff17bcfaad4fe</data>
      <data key="d4">sample_note.md</data>
      <data key="d5">1774674261</data>
